SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 76
BY SENATOR SEABAUGH
COMMENDATIONS. Commends Dewain Strother on being inducted into the 2026 class
of the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame.
1 A CONCURRENT RESOLUTION
2 To commend Dewain Strother on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana Sports
3 Hall of Fame.
4 WHEREAS, each year the Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame in Natchitoches, Louisiana
5 collaborates with the Louisiana Sports Writers Association in selecting a limited number of
6 sports figures who embody the character, skill, talent, and accomplishment worthy of being
7 named to the Hall of Fame; and
8 WHEREAS, the 2026 Louisiana Sports Hall of Fame Induction Class includes
9 Dewain Strother; and
10 WHEREAS, Dewain Strother, a native of Oakdale who was raised in Rapides Parish,
11 has dedicated his life to the development of young athletes and students, serving the
12 community of Sabine Parish for nearly five decades as a teacher, coach, and educational
13 leader; and
14 WHEREAS, as a student-athlete, Dewain Strother distinguished himself on the
15 basketball court as a member of the 1965 state championship team at Plainview High
16 School, where he developed the passion and discipline that would define his life's work; and
17 WHEREAS, after graduating from Northwestern State University, Dewain Strother
18 embarked upon a distinguished career in education and coaching that would leave an
