1 WHEREAS, even in retirement, Strother's passion for mentoring young athletes
2 remained steadfast, and in 2026 he returned to coaching in an assisting role under his former
3 player, Angela Anthony, who succeeded him as head coach of the Lady Black Cats,
4 exemplifying his enduring devotion to the program and the students he served; and
5 WHEREAS, in recognition of his extraordinary career and lasting contributions to
6 high school athletics, Strother was inducted into the Louisiana High School Sports Hall of
7 Fame in 2023; and
8 WHEREAS, through his leadership, integrity, and unwavering dedication to the
9 development of young people, Dewain Strother has left a profound and lasting legacy in
10 Louisiana high school athletics and education.
11 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Legislature of Louisiana does hereby
12 commend Dewain Strother on being inducted into the 2026 class of the Louisiana Sports
13 Hall of Fame.
14 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to
15 Dewain Strother.
